Mexico Stocks: Desarrolladora Homex Declines; Mexichem Gains

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-07-06T20:34:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/mexico-stocks-desarrolladora-homex-declines-mexichem-gains.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index fell 0.5 percent to 36,468.01.  Desarrolladora Homex SAB (HOMEX* MM), Mexico’s largest
homebuilder, dropped 3.1 percent to 46.52 pesos. The company had
its BB- rating put under special review with negative
implications and may be cut if earnings do not improve in the
third quarter,  Standard & Poor’s  said in an e-mailed statement
yesterday.  Mexichem SAB (MEXCHEM* MM),  Latin America ’s biggest maker
of plastic pipes, jumped 3.5 percent to 49.29 pesos. Mexichem
said second-quarter sales gained 36 percent to about 12.2
billion pesos ($1.05 billion), according to a stock exchange
statement that includes preliminary results for the quarter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  